title: Jessa Duggar Gushes Over What a Great Dad Ben Seewald Is
text:
Jessa Duggar Gushes Over What a Great Dad Ben Seewald Is Jenny Erikson 
ben_seewald/Instagram They're still adjusting to life as a family of four, but it looks like the Seewalds are settling right in. Jessa (Duggar) Seewald recently confessed that one of the things making it easier is how hands on Ben has been with their two sons . 
The Counting On stars welcomed their second son, Henry Wilberforce, on February 6. The little guy joined big brother Spurgeon, who is practically still a baby himself at 15 months old. 
More from CafeMom: Unmarried Teen Duggar Sister Rumored to Be Pregnant 
Jessa told PEOPLE magazine that they are already dividing and conquering when it comes caring for their newborn son. She feeds him, and Ben is on diaper duty. "He's gotten so good he could do it with his eyes closed!" she revealed. 
Ben also opened up about having more than one kiddo, saying, "Right now we have two kids and there's two of us, so it's man-to-man coverage." Eventually though, he joked they'll have to "switch it up to a zone defense" when they start adding more to their brood. 
More from CafeMom: Jessa Duggar Opens Up About Her Home Birth Experience With Baby Henry 
It's awesome that Ben is such an involved dad, especially considering that they've talked a lot about their plans for a big family. No word on if Jessa is thinking about having 19 of her own like her mom Michelle, but she's definitely not done with just Spurgeon and Henry. 
Ben and Jessa seem to have transitioned into parenting two so well that we can't help but see them with at least a few more little ones running around.
